Filter Dashboards with URL Parameters in Lightning Experience

Create a custom URL that includes filter values to access your dashboard with filters already set. For example, customize your Opportunity Stages dashboard for each account owner.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To add filters to dashboards you created: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To add filters to dashboards you created in public folders: Edit My Dashboards OR Manage Dashboards in Public Folders
To add filters to dashboards you didnâ€™t create: Manage Dashboards in Public Folders
To add filters to dynamic dashboards: Manage Dynamic Dashboards

Start with a dashboard that includes the filters and values you want. Obtain the base URL by opening the dashboard from Analytics tab or Dashboards tab, then copy it into a text file.

Add the filter to the end of the URL using the format https://MyDomainName.my.salesforce.com/lightning/r/Dashboard/01ZRM0000005jrv2AA/view?queryScope=userFolders&fv0=Closed%20Won&fv1=Acme. The & indicates a new parameter.

Navigate to the dashboard URL with the parameter appended. When it opens, it will open with filter values applied.

These limitations apply:

* Dashboard filter URLs with equals operator are supported but can't use other operators.
* You can't change the field being filtered using URL parameters.
* You can assign at most one value per filter.
* You can't add or delete filters using filter value URL parameters.
title: Customizing Dashboards with URL Parameters
